WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: hr

00:00:00.110 --> 00:00:05.406
Dear young people, yesterday’s Gospel
passage was the one where Jesus

00:00:05.406 --> 00:00:11.184
speaks about communion, comparing that
unity to the vine and its branches.

00:00:11.184 --> 00:00:17.444
Today, in the Gospel, the Lord
calls us to remain in his love.

00:00:17.444 --> 00:00:23.704
We all know very well that, by
definition, God is love, don’t we?

00:00:23.704 --> 00:00:25.149
Are you sure?

00:00:25.149 --> 00:00:27.075
I can’t hear you.

00:00:27.075 --> 00:00:34.298
So, we all know that, by definition,
God is love — but when we look at

00:00:34.298 --> 00:00:40.557
the world and everything that’s
happening in it, do we care more that

00:00:40.557 --> 00:00:44.410
God is love, or that God is just?

00:00:45.210 --> 00:00:49.750
Even though we know that in the
Gospel it says—by definition—that

00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:55.940
God is love, in practice we so often
put more emphasis on God as the

00:00:55.940 --> 00:00:59.242
just one than on God who is love.

00:00:59.242 --> 00:01:05.433
It’s almost as if, deep down, we’re
more inclined to long for a God who

00:01:05.433 --> 00:01:11.211
is “fair”, who will now set wars
right, who will stop this, stop that.

00:01:11.211 --> 00:01:16.990
I get that same feeling even now, when
we look at the political situation.

00:01:17.050 --> 00:01:22.356
Some people even get angry with the
Pope for proclaiming the Gospel of

00:01:22.356 --> 00:01:27.663
peace, the Gospel of love, rather
than some “just” God or some kind

00:01:27.663 --> 00:01:30.521
of religion. And that’s hard for us.

00:01:30.521 --> 00:01:35.828
Understand, because whenever we find
ourselves in a situation, we’d like God to

00:01:35.828 --> 00:01:39.502
be just first, and only then to be love.

00:01:39.502 --> 00:01:41.951
And we often long for that.

00:01:41.951 --> 00:01:43.992
Is our God really almighty?

00:01:43.992 --> 00:01:46.850
How just is he, and how almighty?

00:01:46.850 --> 00:01:48.892
What can He do?

00:01:48.892 --> 00:01:50.935
What can God do?

00:01:50.935 --> 00:01:54.000
What is His strength and power?

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:57.064
And how much can He do?

00:01:57.064 --> 00:02:01.149
So, some will say, God can do anything.

00:02:01.149 --> 00:02:04.725
God can only do what is love.

00:02:04.725 --> 00:02:10.342
Because we need to understand this
evening what I’m talking about,

00:02:10.342 --> 00:02:16.471
and what the fundamental difference
is between an almighty God who can

00:02:16.471 --> 00:02:20.046
love, and a love that is almighty.

00:02:20.046 --> 00:02:22.600
You understand the fundamental difference.

00:02:22.980 --> 00:02:26.335
A God who is almighty, who can love.

00:02:26.335 --> 00:02:30.109
That’s the kind of God
some people long for.

00:02:30.109 --> 00:02:35.561
And then we have God who is
love, and whose love is almighty.

00:02:35.561 --> 00:02:42.691
And that’s why we say that God can do, and
with his power, everything that is love.

00:02:42.691 --> 00:02:45.626
As the Gospel says, God is love.

00:02:45.626 --> 00:02:50.240
And we honour, love, and
cherish the God who is love.

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:56.215
And where do we see this
power and this love which is…

00:02:56.215 --> 00:02:58.154
infinite, which gives itself?

00:02:58.154 --> 00:03:03.970
It’s there when Jesus says in
John’s Gospel, chapter 15: that no

00:03:03.970 --> 00:03:10.755
one has greater love than the one
who lays down his life for others.

00:03:10.755 --> 00:03:14.147
There Jesus calls us friends as well.

00:03:14.147 --> 00:03:18.509
And there Jesus shows us what God is like.

00:03:18.509 --> 00:03:24.325
Is he the all-powerful God,
or is he the God of love?

00:03:24.325 --> 00:03:31.316
Because if Jesus says that there is
no greater love than to lay down one’s

00:03:31.316 --> 00:03:34.113
life, then Jesus did exactly that.

00:03:34.113 --> 00:03:39.706
And now remember the moment in the
Garden of Gethsemane, where Jesus

00:03:39.706 --> 00:03:45.766
goes through his agony, and where
the soldiers came to take him away,

00:03:45.766 --> 00:03:48.562
knowing the end was drawing near.

00:03:48.562 --> 00:03:55.088
Jesus himself even mentions there that
he could call on a legion of angels.

00:03:55.088 --> 00:03:57.885
Jesus really could have done that.

00:03:58.265 --> 00:04:02.837
To avoid the horror of crucifixion,
he could have called on a legion of

00:04:02.837 --> 00:04:07.409
angels, and God would surely have
sent a legion of angels to set him

00:04:07.409 --> 00:04:09.695
free, to protect him and defend him.

00:04:09.695 --> 00:04:12.635
But then what kind of God would that be?

00:04:12.635 --> 00:04:16.227
If, in some situation, Jesus
had done that, he would have

00:04:16.227 --> 00:04:20.147
shown us an all-powerful God,
but not a God who is love.

00:04:20.147 --> 00:04:25.046
As it is, Jesus persists in staying,
and shows us the image of a God

00:04:25.046 --> 00:04:29.945
who is love — not merely just, but
the one who loves to the very end.

00:04:29.945 --> 00:04:34.593
Because we know that Jesus set
himself free out of love—he

00:04:34.593 --> 00:04:37.129
gave himself to the very end.

00:04:37.129 --> 00:04:41.356
You see how much we need
to understand that freedom.

00:04:41.356 --> 00:04:46.850
And this is what even Christians
find hard to accept and grasp: that

00:04:46.850 --> 00:04:48.963
the responsibility is entirely ours.

00:04:48.963 --> 00:04:51.921
We freely choose every gesture of love.

00:04:51.921 --> 00:04:56.993
Because it isn’t love if it’s
forced, if it’s out of necessity,

00:04:56.993 --> 00:05:02.065
if it’s talked into, if it’s
provoked—it has to be pure freedom.

00:05:02.065 --> 00:05:08.257
And you see, Jesus here didn’t make use of
his power, his omnipotence, but of love.

00:05:08.257 --> 00:05:12.514
And he shows us an image
of God who is love.

00:05:12.514 --> 00:05:17.158
And remember that other paragraph
I absolutely love in the Book of

00:05:17.158 --> 00:05:22.188
Revelation, where it describes our
God, how wonderful he is, who is love.

00:05:22.188 --> 00:05:27.607
It says: “I stand at the door and
knock; if anyone opens to me…”

00:05:27.607 --> 00:05:33.025
Here again God shows a love that
respects the freedom of you and me.

00:05:33.225 --> 00:05:37.192
Because God doesn’t force His
way through the door, because

00:05:37.192 --> 00:05:39.175
love doesn’t break things down.

00:05:39.175 --> 00:05:43.936
If love were violent, if it prised
open someone’s heart by force,

00:05:43.936 --> 00:05:46.316
then it wouldn’t be love anymore.

00:05:46.316 --> 00:05:51.870
And God, who is love, says He
stands at the door of our heart.

00:05:51.870 --> 00:05:52.664
He knocks.

00:05:52.664 --> 00:05:53.457
He waits.

00:05:53.457 --> 00:05:55.838
For us to open to Him.

00:05:55.838 --> 00:06:00.598
And you know that lovely parable—about
that painting by the artist who

00:06:00.598 --> 00:06:05.359
captured that very moment of God
knocking at the door—because the door

00:06:05.359 --> 00:06:08.930
had no handle on His side to open it.

00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:14.482
Which means the handle – the possibility
of opening our heart – is on our side.

00:06:14.482 --> 00:06:18.845
People often say, “God is far
away. God can’t be experienced.

00:06:18.845 --> 00:06:21.622
God is this, God is that.” No.

00:06:21.622 --> 00:06:24.795
Don’t go looking for
him somewhere far off.

00:06:24.795 --> 00:06:26.778
The saints say that too.

00:06:26.778 --> 00:06:27.968
God is here.

00:06:27.968 --> 00:06:33.520
It’s just that we’re the ones who
so often get tangled up and don’t

00:06:33.520 --> 00:06:36.693
know how to open our heart to him.

00:06:36.693 --> 00:06:38.676
And that’s what God wants.

00:06:38.676 --> 00:06:41.850
That’s why today it says: God is love.

00:06:41.850 --> 00:06:46.910
And imagine this: Jesus says — I don’t
know whether that sentence encourages you

00:06:46.910 --> 00:06:53.139
— but listen, Jesus says to the disciples:
“As the Father has loved me, so I have

00:06:53.139 --> 00:06:55.475
loved you.” Nothing less, nothing more.

00:06:55.475 --> 00:06:56.253
The same.

00:06:56.253 --> 00:07:00.925
Just as he is loved by the
Father, so Jesus loves us.

00:07:00.925 --> 00:07:06.375
It’s just that sometimes we have this
feeling — but I’ll talk about that later

00:07:06.375 --> 00:07:09.490
— about how to open ourselves to that love.

00:07:09.490 --> 00:07:15.116
I think all of us who are here
want to experience God who is love.

00:07:15.116 --> 00:07:18.492
And many Christians do
too – everyone who would, right?

00:07:18.492 --> 00:07:22.619
But simply, many people struggle
to open themselves up to that

00:07:22.619 --> 00:07:25.245
love and let it into their lives.

00:07:25.245 --> 00:07:30.496
You know, people talk a lot about
that love in every context these days,

00:07:30.496 --> 00:07:35.373
but I like how Pope Francis once,
at the Casa Santa Marta, explained

00:07:35.373 --> 00:07:40.250
a criterion for how to recognise
whether a love is truly real love.

00:07:40.250 --> 00:07:42.984
Is a love truly of God?

00:07:42.984 --> 00:07:44.808
He gave two criteria.

00:07:44.808 --> 00:07:50.733
First, he said that if something is
genuinely God’s love, if it’s real,

00:07:50.733 --> 00:07:58.938
true love of God in us, then love has to
be proved more by deeds than by words.

00:07:58.938 --> 00:08:01.217
We all know that well.

00:08:01.217 --> 00:08:05.320
Love is proved more by
deeds than by words.

00:08:05.320 --> 00:08:10.790
So you can tell me whatever
you like, but show me love.

00:08:10.890 --> 00:08:15.521
God didn’t stop at just talking, at
writing the Bible two thousand years ago.

00:08:15.521 --> 00:08:18.498
He showed it with his life on the cross.

00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:23.791
OK, and he said, “I am love,” and
you can see me, you can see what

00:08:23.791 --> 00:08:29.084
I do — deeds. He loved in a real,
concrete way, he loved to the very end.

00:08:29.084 --> 00:08:31.399
So it didn’t all remain just words.

00:08:31.399 --> 00:08:35.369
And God shows his love — whereas
we sometimes feel the need to

00:08:35.369 --> 00:08:39.670
talk about how we love, but we
don’t show it through our actions.

00:08:39.670 --> 00:08:43.634
God immediately showed through
what He did that He loves us.

00:08:43.634 --> 00:08:49.401
I think all of us, at some point in
life, find ourselves in a situation where

00:08:49.401 --> 00:08:53.366
we’re disappointed—maybe by friends,
maybe by family—by a kind of love

00:08:53.366 --> 00:08:59.133
that stays only at the level of words,
without any real action to back it up.

00:08:59.133 --> 00:09:02.738
You know, we’re all brought up
in our families differently,

00:09:02.738 --> 00:09:04.180
coming from different places.

00:09:04.180 --> 00:09:07.058
And you know there are lots
of different love languages.

00:09:07.058 --> 00:09:10.513
And then you’ve got, I don’t know,
we’re typical Bosnians: it’s just

00:09:10.513 --> 00:09:13.968
taken for granted that we love each
other—God forbid we actually hug.

00:09:13.968 --> 00:09:18.286
But if someone needs help, the whole
family jumps in, we all rush to sort

00:09:18.286 --> 00:09:19.726
the situation out straight away.

00:09:19.726 --> 00:09:24.044
But for someone to give you a calm,
gentle hug or something like that—no, no.

00:09:24.044 --> 00:09:26.060
That’s just how we were brought up.

00:09:26.720 --> 00:09:30.987
I was in Italy, and I’ve got that
sort of experience from Italy.

00:09:30.987 --> 00:09:34.927
In one part of Italy, love is very
affectionate again: there’s constant

00:09:34.927 --> 00:09:37.553
hugging, constant cuddling, constant
encouragement, constant flattering with

00:09:37.553 --> 00:09:41.821
words, but then perhaps in a concrete
situation, when you actually need help,

00:09:41.821 --> 00:09:44.447
it’s withheld from you in a different way.

00:09:44.447 --> 00:09:48.386
That’s why I say there are many
love languages, but Pope Francis

00:09:48.386 --> 00:09:49.700
mentions those two criteria.

00:09:49.700 --> 00:09:53.645
Love is proved by deeds,
not by words—by words.

00:09:53.645 --> 00:09:58.468
And secondly, he says that
love comes from the fact that

00:09:58.468 --> 00:10:01.098
communication is truly part of love.

00:10:01.098 --> 00:10:02.413
Because love communicates.

00:10:02.413 --> 00:10:05.044
That is, God loved and communicated.

00:10:05.044 --> 00:10:09.428
He communicated through his deeds,
he communicated through his words.

00:10:09.428 --> 00:10:13.373
Communication is, I say,
an integral part of love.

00:10:13.373 --> 00:10:19.072
If there is no communication, for
example we Christians can go on about

00:10:19.072 --> 00:10:25.648
how Christian we are, how good we
are, how devoted we are to God, and

00:10:25.648 --> 00:10:30.909
yet we don’t communicate with our
fellow man, with a work colleague,

00:10:30.909 --> 00:10:33.540
with a friend, with a spouse.

00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:35.625
Do you understand?

00:10:35.625 --> 00:10:38.476
We don’t communicate with the person.

00:10:38.476 --> 00:10:43.227
And then love isn’t concrete,
it can’t be lived out.

00:10:43.227 --> 00:10:49.879
True love of God is shown in
deeds, as the Pope says, and that

00:10:49.879 --> 00:10:51.780
love, in itself, communicates.

00:10:51.780 --> 00:10:56.531
It’s true that Christian
love, real love of God, isn’t

00:10:56.531 --> 00:10:59.382
always the way we imagine it.

00:10:59.382 --> 00:11:04.609
For each of us, God’s love
can also be something that

00:11:04.609 --> 00:11:07.460
happens as a love that hurts.

00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:09.065
That’s what Jesus showed.

00:11:09.065 --> 00:11:13.370
So, we as Christians can often
expect it, because Jesus prepared

00:11:13.370 --> 00:11:19.241
us for it and warned us that we must
go through what He went through.

00:11:19.241 --> 00:11:24.329
Because what’s asked of us is that
true, authentic love: that we can

00:11:24.329 --> 00:11:29.809
love, that we can forgive those who
don’t love us, those who hate us,

00:11:29.809 --> 00:11:35.680
those who may persecute us, who may
trample on us in one way or another.

00:11:36.050 --> 00:11:41.666
And that’s why Christian love is
sometimes difficult and painful, yet free.

00:11:41.666 --> 00:11:44.943
Because, again, you do
everything in freedom.

00:11:44.943 --> 00:11:50.092
Each of us, in such situations,
chooses either love or hatred.

00:11:50.092 --> 00:11:54.772
Until a person recognises within
themselves why they should forgive

00:11:54.772 --> 00:11:59.453
someone, or love them, or hate
them—until they themselves understand

00:11:59.453 --> 00:12:05.070
what they’re doing to themselves by
that—Jesus didn’t say for no reason

00:12:05.070 --> 00:12:11.155
that we should forgive and love,
because in that way love is multiplied.

00:12:11.155 --> 00:12:17.327
Because if my heart isn’t free, if you’re
not clean of hatred and of other feelings

00:12:17.327 --> 00:12:23.499
towards someone, then you can’t say that
your love is what we said a moment ago:

00:12:23.499 --> 00:12:26.199
proven by deeds, and that it communicates.

00:12:26.199 --> 00:12:29.285
That’s why Christian love
can sometimes be hard.

00:12:29.285 --> 00:12:34.300
It’s hard if we stay on the
surface, on the merely human level.

00:12:34.300 --> 00:12:39.314
But for us that grace, like the
grace Jesus had, comes from God.

00:12:40.015 --> 00:12:40.775
From God.

00:12:40.775 --> 00:12:46.859
So the Lord gives us the grace of the
Holy Spirit and the strength to be

00:12:46.859 --> 00:12:49.521
able to love even our greatest enemies.

00:12:49.521 --> 00:12:55.225
And if nothing else, I’m sure that
even if we don’t yet have that heroic

00:12:55.225 --> 00:13:00.929
act of loving our enemies so much and
forgiving, we’ve been given the grace at

00:13:00.929 --> 00:13:03.211
least to protect ourselves from hatred.

00:13:03.211 --> 00:13:04.351
To protect ourselves.

00:13:04.351 --> 00:13:08.915
Because sometimes it seems strange
to me that people choose to hate.

00:13:09.755 --> 00:13:13.942
Because I always… I say: if
you won’t forgive someone else,

00:13:13.942 --> 00:13:15.465
you haven’t punished them.

00:13:15.465 --> 00:13:16.607
You’ve punished yourself.

00:13:16.607 --> 00:13:21.175
Because every time you stay stuck
in something, in some open wound,

00:13:21.175 --> 00:13:24.982
in some unresolved relationship, you
haven’t harmed that other person.

00:13:24.982 --> 00:13:26.885
You haven’t harmed God either.

00:13:26.885 --> 00:13:28.027
You’ve harmed yourself.

00:13:28.027 --> 00:13:32.976
That’s why it’s important always to
keep in mind that God, through this

00:13:32.976 --> 00:13:38.306
commandment… because very few people can
say, “How can your God be love?”, and

00:13:38.306 --> 00:13:43.255
yet today’s Gospel we’re reading says:
Jesus says, “I give you a commandment.”

00:13:44.055 --> 00:13:48.652
How is it that if God is love and
freedom, He gives us a commandment?

00:13:48.652 --> 00:13:51.717
It sounds interesting, but God is
emphasising what matters—what is

00:13:51.717 --> 00:13:56.621
so good for us that we should hold
to it as if it were a commandment,

00:13:56.621 --> 00:13:58.460
so we don’t lose our way.

00:13:58.460 --> 00:14:02.445
Because today it’s easy to get lost
in relationships with other people, in

00:14:02.445 --> 00:14:06.429
emotions—some of us are more emotional,
some less, some… But a person can

00:14:06.429 --> 00:14:08.575
quickly lose themselves in all of that.

00:14:08.615 --> 00:14:12.218
Especially when you get battered from
all sides, knocked about, dragged

00:14:12.218 --> 00:14:16.478
through it, wounded—then you end
up like a lost soul in the fog.

00:14:16.478 --> 00:14:20.409
You don’t know where you’re going,
you’ve just turned up, set off…

00:14:20.409 --> 00:14:23.030
what am I doing, why am I living?

00:14:23.030 --> 00:14:26.634
And you’ll see all of that—especially
you young people—where you get

00:14:26.634 --> 00:14:29.255
discouraged from fighting, from
hoping, from moving forwards.

00:14:29.255 --> 00:14:33.515
It’s strange to me that young people
don’t have dreams, don’t have desires.

00:14:34.555 --> 00:14:35.182
And where?

00:14:35.182 --> 00:14:36.751
Where did you lose it?

00:14:36.751 --> 00:14:40.203
Well, here you are – it
got lost in all of this.

00:14:40.203 --> 00:14:43.968
When certain life situations have been
slapping you about, wounding you, and

00:14:43.968 --> 00:14:46.165
you haven’t managed to surface from it.

00:14:46.165 --> 00:14:49.930
You haven’t managed to rise
above it and sort out all those

00:14:49.930 --> 00:14:51.185
things, to protect yourself.

00:14:51.185 --> 00:14:55.265
And then you’re still floating in it – in
that situation, in that relationship.

00:14:55.265 --> 00:14:59.971
Look, some of you split up with a
girlfriend or a boyfriend and you can’t

00:14:59.971 --> 00:15:04.364
get out of those wounds for years, and
it’s just drama, drama, drama, drama.

00:15:05.805 --> 00:15:10.901
I know it hurts, but,
mate, love isn’t violent.

00:15:10.901 --> 00:15:14.865
If someone doesn’t want you, accept it.

00:15:14.865 --> 00:15:21.661
If someone wants to leave you,
have a bit of self-respect too.

00:15:21.661 --> 00:15:28.456
If someone rejects your love, then
thanks, bye mate, there are others.

00:15:28.456 --> 00:15:29.023
Right?

00:15:29.023 --> 00:15:34.119
So, love can sometimes
make you laugh as well.

00:15:34.119 --> 00:15:41.481
But look, what’s also important,
as a third point: we say God is

00:15:41.481 --> 00:15:48.843
love—and He is love—but sometimes
we need to see whether our love is

00:15:48.843 --> 00:15:51.675
in order, pure, towards ourselves.

00:15:51.954 --> 00:15:56.066
You know there are those kinds
of disordered love — especially

00:15:56.066 --> 00:15:57.711
disordered love towards ourselves.

00:15:57.711 --> 00:16:02.644
Because I think it’s fundamental for
a good relationship with God, and

00:16:02.644 --> 00:16:06.756
fundamental for a good relationship
with someone else — whether it’s

00:16:06.756 --> 00:16:11.690
friendship, whether it’s married couples
or anything else — to have a good,

00:16:11.690 --> 00:16:14.156
healthy attitude and love for yourself.

00:16:14.156 --> 00:16:17.035
But that’s where things
can become disordered.

00:16:17.035 --> 00:16:20.503
And that most often
goes in two directions.

00:16:20.503 --> 00:16:23.971
You’ve got that… disordered,
self-important kind of self-love.

00:16:23.971 --> 00:16:26.573
Everything has to submit to me.

00:16:26.573 --> 00:16:28.307
Everything revolves around me.

00:16:28.307 --> 00:16:35.677
So if it isn’t the way I want it,
the way I expect it, then again there

00:16:35.677 --> 00:16:37.845
are problems, again there’s drama.

00:16:37.845 --> 00:16:41.747
That’s one of the disordered
attitudes of “love” someone

00:16:41.747 --> 00:16:43.481
can develop towards themselves.

00:16:43.481 --> 00:16:49.551
You know those people who are always
right, and always the ones in need,

00:16:49.551 --> 00:16:54.753
everything has to revolve around
them — and if it doesn’t, that’s where

00:16:54.753 --> 00:16:57.354
all relationships come to a halt.

00:16:57.494 --> 00:17:03.730
If you won’t play by his rules, or hers,
that’s where relationships break down.

00:17:03.730 --> 00:17:08.630
And that’s when we can see that
something isn’t quite right.

00:17:08.630 --> 00:17:13.975
Because we become a bit self-important
towards ourselves, and maybe put ourselves

00:17:13.975 --> 00:17:17.539
on a level we’re not really up to.

00:17:17.539 --> 00:17:23.775
But then there’s the other extreme,
which is perhaps an even harder one when

00:17:23.775 --> 00:17:28.675
it comes to experiencing God’s love:
in some people, it’s self-contempt.

00:17:30.175 --> 00:17:34.470
So you’re constantly self-loathing:
blaming yourself, hating things about

00:17:34.470 --> 00:17:38.289
yourself, not accepting yourself,
criticising yourself, being dissatisfied,

00:17:38.289 --> 00:17:43.540
and there’s this continual contempt
for your own attitudes and decisions.

00:17:43.540 --> 00:17:46.881
Those people are the hardest to help.

00:17:46.881 --> 00:17:52.609
And look, if someone has nothing but
contempt for themselves, it’s hard

00:17:52.609 --> 00:17:58.814
to bring them closer to God, who is
love, because they’re always doubting.

00:17:58.814 --> 00:18:04.065
If you despise yourself, you always
think you haven’t deserved love.

00:18:04.425 --> 00:18:08.838
How often do we hear it when people
say, “Oh, I don’t deserve it, I’m

00:18:08.838 --> 00:18:12.958
not worthy to be forgiven. Does God
love me, after what I’ve done?” But

00:18:12.958 --> 00:18:17.077
listen, my dear: there’s nothing you
can do that would make God move away

00:18:17.077 --> 00:18:21.197
from you. There’s nothing you can do
that would make God stop loving you.

00:18:21.197 --> 00:18:25.316
Even if you’re the greatest sinner, even
if you’ve made the worst decisions in

00:18:25.316 --> 00:18:27.965
your life, God does not turn away from us.

00:18:28.245 --> 00:18:32.546
Look, it’s interesting: it
says the devil knows us so well

00:18:32.546 --> 00:18:34.892
and he knows our names too.

00:18:34.892 --> 00:18:39.584
And there’s that saying that
the devil doesn’t call us by our

00:18:39.584 --> 00:18:42.321
name, he calls us by our sin.

00:18:42.321 --> 00:18:45.058
But you see, with God it’s different.

00:18:45.058 --> 00:18:49.750
God says there in Holy Scripture, he
calls out, “Jacob”, “Israel” — meaning,

00:18:49.750 --> 00:18:55.225
he calls by name: “I have called
you by your name; you are mine.”

00:18:55.445 --> 00:19:00.259
So, you see, God calls us by
our name, not by our sins.

00:19:00.259 --> 00:19:03.592
Because He loves us,
because we are His children.

00:19:03.592 --> 00:19:08.036
And Satan, who also knows our
names, calls us by our sins.

00:19:08.036 --> 00:19:10.999
And you can see what the difference is.

00:19:10.999 --> 00:19:16.184
The difference is this as well:
God wants us to burn for Him, and

00:19:16.184 --> 00:19:18.776
the devil wants us to burn out.

00:19:18.776 --> 00:19:19.517
That’s it.

00:19:19.517 --> 00:19:25.072
And that’s why I say we have to keep
working at it somehow, and begin

00:19:25.072 --> 00:19:27.665
first of all, right from the start.

00:19:27.945 --> 00:19:33.778
On having a good, healthy relationship,
and the way we live towards ourselves.

00:19:33.778 --> 00:19:39.162
Then it will develop differently with
God too, and with our neighbours.

00:19:39.162 --> 00:19:42.751
Today that image of God is very distorted.

00:19:42.751 --> 00:19:48.585
You know, you often hear it — for
example, brother, what I said: how

00:19:48.585 --> 00:19:55.764
Satan calls us by our sins, not by our
name, and how he keeps convincing us

00:19:55.764 --> 00:19:58.905
that we’re not worthy of God’s love.

00:19:59.025 --> 00:20:04.267
And Jesus says today, “Remain in
my love, and I in you.” That means:

00:20:04.267 --> 00:20:09.135
don’t go anywhere else, don’t look for
comfort elsewhere, don’t look for hope

00:20:09.135 --> 00:20:11.381
elsewhere — I’m here, stay with me.

00:20:11.381 --> 00:20:12.505
Remain in me.

00:20:15.225 --> 00:20:19.657
It’s interesting, if you remember that
scene when Peter comes before Jesus,

00:20:19.657 --> 00:20:25.199
throws himself at his feet and says,
“Lord, go away from me; I’m a sinful

00:20:25.199 --> 00:20:27.785
man.” And where does that come from?

00:20:27.925 --> 00:20:32.333
Because Satan convinced him that he was
sinful, that he wasn’t worthy of Jesus.

00:20:32.333 --> 00:20:37.056
And the poor man says, “Go away from
me, Lord, I’m not worthy, because I’m

00:20:37.056 --> 00:20:41.465
a sinner.” Because Peter believed what
Satan tries to convince all of us of:

00:20:41.465 --> 00:20:45.873
that we’re not worthy, and that when
we’re sinful we should live apart from

00:20:45.873 --> 00:20:49.967
God. But the reality is different. God
calls us precisely then: “Come, let

00:20:49.967 --> 00:20:54.690
me cleanse you; come, let me heal you,
let me strengthen you, let me love

00:20:54.690 --> 00:20:57.210
you, let me carry you on my shoulders.”

00:20:58.910 --> 00:21:03.377
However, when Jesus emphasises this
– “remain in my love” – how is it that

00:21:03.377 --> 00:21:08.876
all of a sudden we’re seeing such an
exodus from the Church? How is it that,

00:21:08.876 --> 00:21:13.688
even though we know all these wonderful
things about God’s love, so many people

00:21:13.688 --> 00:21:18.500
are leaving the Church, not going to
church at all – everything has gone cold?

00:21:18.500 --> 00:21:21.936
And then you sometimes hear
suggestions: people say the Church

00:21:21.936 --> 00:21:25.030
should change something, the
Church should do something new.

00:21:25.030 --> 00:21:28.742
Maybe the Church ought to modernise a bit.

00:21:28.742 --> 00:21:34.311
Of course it should use everything
that’s good for proclaiming the Gospel.

00:21:34.311 --> 00:21:37.095
But God, by definition, is love.

00:21:37.095 --> 00:21:38.952
He doesn’t need PR.

00:21:38.952 --> 00:21:44.520
Because you know who uses PR—these days
it’s fashionable in every company—to

00:21:44.520 --> 00:21:49.161
advertise something, to sell something,
to persuade people of something,

00:21:49.161 --> 00:21:52.410
regardless of whether it’s good or not.

00:21:52.410 --> 00:21:58.049
Rather, my job is to persuade
you to buy this, or to take it.

00:21:58.049 --> 00:22:03.689
It’s the same as what’s being pushed
today in the Church as well: “Come

00:22:03.689 --> 00:22:10.134
on, get a move on, do something, shake
things up a bit, hire experts.” But God

00:22:10.134 --> 00:22:12.954
doesn’t need that. God doesn’t need it.

00:22:12.954 --> 00:22:14.162
Because what happens?

00:22:14.162 --> 00:22:20.204
That kind of PR for the Church, PR
for God, has produced bad fruit in

00:22:20.204 --> 00:22:24.635
some parts of the Church – across
our continent, across Europe – where

00:22:24.635 --> 00:22:26.650
we see churches shutting down.

00:22:26.650 --> 00:22:27.522
And why?

00:22:27.522 --> 00:22:32.759
Because they went to listen to
the experts, and then they dealt

00:22:32.759 --> 00:22:37.995
with it like this: the truth gets
adjusted so that it’s acceptable.

00:22:37.995 --> 00:22:39.304
God is truth.

00:22:39.304 --> 00:22:44.540
The truth can’t be adapted to
society just to make it acceptable.

00:22:44.540 --> 00:22:45.850
So, that’s wrong.

00:22:45.850 --> 00:22:48.031
That’s where it goes off.

00:22:48.031 --> 00:22:50.650
It means Jesus’ messages get changed.

00:23:02.889 --> 00:23:10.642
And then you see how both the direction
and the proclamation can go wrong if we

00:23:10.642 --> 00:23:14.033
start promoting and pushing what we think.

00:23:14.033 --> 00:23:21.301
But we don’t need to change the content
of faith, or the Gospel, or God.

00:23:21.301 --> 00:23:22.754
God is love.

00:23:22.754 --> 00:23:25.661
Nothing can be better than that.

00:23:25.661 --> 00:23:28.568
What needs to change is us.

00:23:28.568 --> 00:23:30.991
We need to change ourselves.

00:23:30.991 --> 00:23:37.290
So if God is love, I must
pray: “Lord, keep me in you.”

00:23:37.290 --> 00:23:39.358
To remain in my love.

00:23:39.358 --> 00:23:41.840
I won’t do anything to you.

00:23:41.840 --> 00:23:44.736
I can only make you happy, content.

00:23:44.736 --> 00:23:50.113
But it’s the person who won’t let
themselves be loved, who rejects love,

00:23:50.113 --> 00:23:53.009
and that needs to be stated clearly.

00:23:53.009 --> 00:23:58.387
That has nothing to do with our
preaching, with adapting, with the way

00:23:58.387 --> 00:24:03.765
we’ll present the Gospel today; it’s
that a person doesn’t want to change.

00:24:03.765 --> 00:24:08.302
It says very clearly in the
Gospel: I came, but people

00:24:08.302 --> 00:24:10.364
loved darkness more than light.

00:24:10.364 --> 00:24:14.076
That’s what Jesus says: they
loved darkness more; they

00:24:14.076 --> 00:24:16.551
loved lies more than the truth.

00:24:16.551 --> 00:24:21.913
And that’s why I’m saying people leave
for that reason — not because the

00:24:21.913 --> 00:24:26.862
Church isn’t modern, not because it
hasn’t changed the way it proclaims

00:24:26.862 --> 00:24:32.225
the message, but because, at heart, a
person doesn’t want to change themselves.

00:24:32.225 --> 00:24:35.605
Because they love darkness more.

00:25:02.225 --> 00:25:07.197
People say things even though they’re not
at all like how they describe themselves.

00:25:07.197 --> 00:25:12.170
But when you’re standing in prayer
before God, ask: “God, what am I really

00:25:12.170 --> 00:25:17.142
like?” You know, I’ve noticed that myself
too sometimes when I come before God.

00:25:17.142 --> 00:25:22.115
There are those moments when you truly
just fall apart, you break down before

00:25:22.115 --> 00:25:27.088
Jesus — especially when you begin to grasp
that sense, that realisation, that God is

00:25:27.088 --> 00:25:30.285
love, that He loves you just as you are.

00:25:30.285 --> 00:25:35.860
And in a person there’s simply born
that feeling of repentance, and a

00:25:35.860 --> 00:25:38.863
desire to draw even closer to God.

00:25:38.863 --> 00:25:44.868
But when someone is full of themselves,
when they don’t allow God to love

00:25:44.868 --> 00:25:47.441
them, there’s no joy in that.

00:25:47.441 --> 00:25:49.586
You can force it, sure.

00:25:49.586 --> 00:25:54.733
Look, yesterday I was preaching in
Dubrava, I was leading a spiritual

00:25:54.733 --> 00:25:59.451
renewal, and I used that comparison:
the vine and its branches.

00:25:59.451 --> 00:26:02.025
What a brilliant comparison that is.

00:26:03.045 --> 00:26:06.560
But the Lord wants us
to bear fruit every day.

00:26:06.560 --> 00:26:10.778
I was explaining that yesterday too;
perhaps someone was at the retreat

00:26:10.778 --> 00:26:13.590
and has heard me for the second time.

00:26:13.590 --> 00:26:18.159
My dear people, most of us in
the Church are living off the

00:26:18.159 --> 00:26:19.917
old glory of our spirituality.

00:26:19.917 --> 00:26:26.244
That is, we fall back on ten years ago
when I encountered God — oh, how I was on

00:26:26.244 --> 00:26:28.705
fire then, how I really felt something.

00:26:28.705 --> 00:26:33.621
Oh, how I could pray ten years
ago – ten years ago I was able to

00:26:33.621 --> 00:26:36.243
pray, and now I can’t pray at all.

00:26:36.243 --> 00:26:38.538
But we still keep going to church.

00:26:38.538 --> 00:26:41.160
We stopped long ago praying
fervently, loving fervently,

00:26:41.160 --> 00:26:42.143
sacrificing fervently, fighting.

00:26:42.143 --> 00:26:47.060
We’re still in the church, we still go
on Sundays, but this world has somehow

00:26:47.060 --> 00:26:50.993
sucked us in so much – problems,
worries, everything – that all of a

00:26:50.993 --> 00:26:52.960
sudden we’ve drifted away from God.

00:26:53.980 --> 00:26:56.416
Because Jesus says: he looks for fruit.

00:26:56.416 --> 00:27:02.334
God doesn’t ask what you gave ten years
ago, but what the fruits of love are today

00:27:02.334 --> 00:27:04.770
— what has grown today in your heart.

00:27:04.770 --> 00:27:09.991
Can anyone make use of some fruit of
love from my heart, from your heart,

00:27:09.991 --> 00:27:12.080
today, among the people we’ve met?

00:27:12.080 --> 00:27:13.820
Was there any fruit today?

00:27:13.820 --> 00:27:15.561
Or was it only evil?

00:27:15.561 --> 00:27:17.997
Because we must — Jesus asks for it.

00:27:17.997 --> 00:27:21.826
I heard that yesterday in the
Gospel: he says every day.

00:27:21.826 --> 00:27:26.700
And he even says, if it doesn’t bear
fruit — chop — off with its head.

00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:31.401
So, fruit is being asked of us;
we’re meant to bear it every day,

00:27:31.401 --> 00:27:35.068
to wake up a bit and not live off
the old glory of our spirituality.

00:27:35.068 --> 00:27:36.779
That’s what I’m saying in those moments.

00:27:36.779 --> 00:27:39.956
If we’ve been given something,
the Lord has given it to us, and

00:27:39.956 --> 00:27:41.912
it has to be lived out every day.

00:27:41.912 --> 00:27:45.333
We should fight each day to bear
fruit, not reel off to God things

00:27:45.333 --> 00:27:49.244
from 10, 15, 20 years ago: “Back
then I was at my best,” and now I

00:27:49.244 --> 00:27:51.200
just carry on going to church, but I…

00:27:52.740 --> 00:27:57.698
It’s sad to see a Christian
who’s dry, who’s withered.

00:27:57.698 --> 00:28:02.656
Imagine that young shoot — that’s
you and me — wilting every

00:28:02.656 --> 00:28:05.631
day and not bearing any fruit.

00:28:05.631 --> 00:28:12.572
And there are… loads of Christians who are
spiritually, spiritually cut off from God.

00:28:12.572 --> 00:28:13.564
Cut off.

00:28:13.564 --> 00:28:16.043
Yes, they’re present in church.

00:28:16.043 --> 00:28:18.026
Yes, they’re declared Christians.

00:28:18.026 --> 00:28:23.480
Yes, they’re the ones who welcome
the priest at Christmas, for

00:28:23.480 --> 00:28:25.960
the blessing of their homes.

00:28:26.580 --> 00:28:31.855
But, realistically, both the world and
God will recognise us by our fruits.

00:28:31.855 --> 00:28:37.943
We can present ourselves to one another
however we like — as good, as holy, as

00:28:37.943 --> 00:28:40.784
sinful — and have all sorts of opinions.

00:28:40.784 --> 00:28:42.813
But the fruits are there.

00:28:42.813 --> 00:28:43.625
The fruits.

00:28:43.625 --> 00:28:49.306
When a Christian today is missing those
basic fruits — even just a little spirit

00:28:49.306 --> 00:28:55.800
of joy, a spirit of prayer — it drives
me mad when someone says they can’t pray.

00:28:55.920 --> 00:28:58.126
Well, you can’t if your faith is weak.

00:28:58.126 --> 00:29:00.608
You should let the Holy
Spirit pray within you.

00:29:00.608 --> 00:29:02.263
Then you’ll see it is possible.

00:29:02.263 --> 00:29:05.573
But if you won’t let the Holy
Spirit in, of course every

00:29:05.573 --> 00:29:06.952
prayer feels like a burden.

00:29:06.952 --> 00:29:08.331
Because you’re forcing it yourself.

00:29:08.331 --> 00:29:12.468
You need to let yourself go a bit, let
the Spirit’s fervour carry you, let

00:29:12.468 --> 00:29:16.606
God’s love sweep you up, so you just
can’t stop thanking God for the whole

00:29:16.606 --> 00:29:19.640
day that’s been so wonderful today,
despite the crosses, the problems.

00:29:20.440 --> 00:29:22.645
No, honestly, we can’t even pray.

00:29:22.645 --> 00:29:25.217
So I say: the spirit of joy.

00:29:25.217 --> 00:29:29.995
Then what are we going to stir
up in ourselves, and in others?

00:29:29.995 --> 00:29:33.671
The spirit of perseverance,
and so on and so on.

00:29:33.671 --> 00:29:38.081
We can, I’m saying, speak to
one another, but we need it.

00:29:38.081 --> 00:29:38.449
Yes.

00:29:38.449 --> 00:29:41.389
We prepare ourselves and
we examine the spirits.

00:29:41.389 --> 00:29:42.124
People, pray.

00:29:42.124 --> 00:29:47.270
Pray for mercy and for the gift of
the Holy Spirit—for whatever you need.

00:29:47.270 --> 00:29:51.102
Whether it’s the gift of prayer,
of love, I don’t know — whatever

00:29:51.102 --> 00:29:53.657
you need, God will give it to us.

00:29:53.657 --> 00:29:57.490
Because God wants us to remain
in Him and to bear fruit.

00:29:57.490 --> 00:29:57.810
Amen.

